ersity of wales and is a fellow of the institute of electrical engineers and of the royal academy of engineering in  he was appointed an officer of the order of the british empire and in  as part of the queens birthday honours he was awarded a knighthood he was also appointed patron of the european cancer stem cell research institute in  terry matthews  wikipedia terry matthews from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search sir terry matthews kbe freng fiee born terence hedley matthews   june  age  newport wales uk residence ottawa ontario canada citizenship canadian british alma mater swansea university occupation chairman of mitel chairman of wesley clover net worth  billion  title sir spouses ann matthews children  karen sparks b  trevor matthews b  sir terence hedley matthews kbe frengfiee born  june  is a welshcanadian business magnate serial hightech entrepreneur and wales first billionaire he has founded or funded over  companies in the high tech communications field most notably mitel and newbridge networks he is the chairman of mitel wesley clover and the swansea bay city region board he owns the celtic manor resort krp properties the brookstreet hotel and the marshes golf club contents  early life  career  mitel  newbridge networks  return to mitel  other businesses  wales  philanthropy  honours  personal life  see also  references  external links early lifeedit matthews was born in newport south wales at the then lydia beynon maternity hospital matthews returned as an adult to include the manor house that housed the hospital within the celtic manor resort he grew up in the town of newbridge caerphilly he studied at swansea university and received a bachelors degree in electronics in  careeredit after an apprenticeship at british telecoms research lab at martlesham heath matthews left britain and joined microsystems international a chipmaking operation affiliated with northern telecom which became nortel networks in ottawa canada miteledit matthews first enterprise was started in collaboration with fellow briton and microsystems employee michael cowpland in  to raise seed money for future enterprises they had planned the pair intended to import and sell electric lawnmowers built in the uk conventionally and as well accounts by terry matthews the name mitel is thought to be a contraction of mike and terrys lawnmowers however cowpland is quoted as saying that it stands for mike and terry electronics this first endeavour was a fiasco the shipping company carrying the first batch lost the container when the lawnmowers finally arrived the ground was covered with snow in the canadian winter and no one would buy them matthews later said that taught me a key lesson — the importance of timing the shipping company lost the lawnmowers by the time they showed up noone wanted them as you cant cut grass when its covered with snow mitel became a technology consultancy company run from home to the various companies around ottawas emerging hightech district mitels clients included the national research council the communications research centre and a handful of pioneering startups including shl systemhouse which was later purchased by eds and now is part of hp and quasar systems now cognos obtaining funding from a  bank loan and as well from their own savings and a group of angel investors notably kent plumley the two developed a telephony dtmf tone receiver based on cowplands phd thesis this was a major advance in the technology since they were able to sell receivers at a fraction of the cost of competing versions while gaining returns of  additionally mitel later became a chip manufacturer with the acquisition of the silek foundry in bromont quebec later the pair realized that the then new technology of microprocessors and other semiconductor devices would make a similar change in the market for small pbxs the sx pbx launched to immense success being cheaper to purchase quicker to install and far more functional mitel became one of the more successful manufacturers of small pbx systems and telecom semiconductors in the world floating on the new york stock exchange in  in  british telecom bought a controlling interest in mitel cowpland would later form the company that became corel and matthews later founded newbridge networks newbridge networksedit in  matthews drove newbridge to become a leader in the worldwide data networking industry manufacturing data communications products especially atm devices and routers in  the company employed more than  employees with recorded fy  revenue of  billion later in  newbridge was acquired by alcatel for  billion matthews personal stake in newbridge was valued at over a billion dollars and as a result of the transaction he became the largest single shareholder in alcatel return to miteledit in  he reacquired the mitel pbx business and company name taking it private he has invested heavily  million by  in mitel to turn it into a broadband communications company the company has made significant investments in enterprise voice over ip telephony technology mitels manufacturing business was spun off as breconridge the company acquired intertel in april  mitel went public again in  mitel announced the purchase of aastra technologies in november  mitel announced the purchase of mavenir systems in march  mitel announced the purchase of polycom in april  however the deal fell through and polycom instead merged with private equity firm siris capital group other businessesedit wesley clover – matthews is the founder and chairman of the investment group headquartered in ottawa canada wesley clover has offices in the united states united kingdom india china and russia investments in information and communication technologies digital media and real estate celtic manor resort  a high class resort with a golf club attached to it in newport south wales krp properties  matthews company which manages land and buildings in the kanata north business park brookstreet hotel  hotel in ottawa ontario canada marshes golf club  golf club in ottawa ontario canada march networks  provider of ip video solutions ipo on  april  this venture was the first successful high tech ipo in the ottawa area since  bridgewater systems – a software company enabling mobile service providers to personalize manage and deliver applications acquired by amdocs in june  for  million ubiquity software – developer of sipims application server software platform which was acquired by avaya in feb  for about us m and is the basis of avayas next generation solutions convedia – a maker of voipims media servers which was acquired by radisys in  for us  million and is the basis of radisys mediaengine solutions celtic house – matthews and roger maggs cofounded celtic house international corporation chic in  the objective was to invest in emerging high technology companies primarily in the uk and canada in  chic was restructured to form celtic house venture partners a limited partnership owned and managed independent of matthews newport networks  a maker of large carriergrade session border controllers on  march  newport networks with its two remaining employees delisted from the aim this is despite having announced twelve months earlier that the company had signed a major oem agreement which was expected to substantially increase its product sales the company has subsequently been wound up and liquidated alacrity incubator and accelerator program  matthews founded alacrity in  along with his son owen matthews and simon gibson alacrity is a nonprofit organization aimed at connecting established western canadian companies with venture capitalists and investment firms additionally matthews serves on the board of directors for a number of high tech companies and chairs solace systems  and counterpath corporation walesedit matthews spends a considerable amount of time in his native wales working on such ventures as the celtic manor resort a leisure complex in newport near the south wales coast chosen to host the  ryder cup golf tournament and the  nato summit the celtic manor hosted the isps handa wales open for  years the original celtic manor hotel was formerly a maternity hospital and is matthews birthplace matthews bought celtic manor in  ploughing £m into the project firstly the th century manor house was renovated while in  plans were unveiled to develop two new golf courses and a convention centre between the manor and the river usk matthews had become friends with golf course architect the late robert trent jones snr whose family roots were in aberystwyth work began on the roman road course in  named after the main route connecting the former roman fortress of caerleon with the town of caerwent which crosses the land in  the yard coldra woods golf course was started as well as the £m golf clubhouse hotel celtic manor was hotel of the year in  and won two european design awards in   one for the interior designers goff associates and one for its spa from the international spa association matthews commented that i think the resort can act as a magnet to draw new investment into wales from across the uk and overseas i did my best to put up a building that you can see from the west end of london and i didnt come far short of it in september  matthews was appointed chairman of the swansea bay city region board the swansea bay city region board is backing a swansea tidal lagoon project in january  he purchased the hilton hotel in newport philanthropyedit matthews founded the wesley clover foundation a notforprofit philanthropic corporation that supports entrepreneurship healthcare education and community initiatives the foundation leased the properties formerly known as the nepean national equestrian park and the ottawa municipal campground to create wesley clover parks matthews hosts an annual gala lumière that has raised over  million for charity honoursedit in  he was appointed an officer of the order of the british empire obe in  he was elected as a fellow of the royal academy of engineering in june  he was conferred the honour of knight commander of the order of the british empire kbe in the queens birthday honours he was knighted by hm the queen at an investiture in buckingham palace matthews has received honorary doctorates from the university of wales glamorgan and swansea and carleton university in  he was awarded an honorary degree doctor of engineering from the university of bath in  he was appointed patron of the cancer stem cell research institute at cardiff university personal lifeedit his daughter karen is executive director at wesley clover parks his youngest son trevor is an actor founder and ceo of brookstreet pictures see alsoedit list of canadians list of welsh people list of people from ottawa list of canadians by net worth referencesedit  newsroom  board of directors  dr terence h matthews mitel   about us  history wesley clover   a b canada’s richest people terry matthews canadian business  december    a b list of fellows royal academy of engineering retrieved  july    forbes face terry matthews forbes  may  retrieved  july    a b terry matthews a wellconnected celt the guardian  october  retrieved  july    nows the time to be a tech startup says sir terry matthews  june  retrieved  july    theres a revolution going on says terry matthews of tech industry ottawa business journal retrieved  july    a b c sir terry matthews profit magazine  june  retrieved  july    a b c how to turn  into billions energy hard work passion waterloo region record  may  retrieved  june    craig bailey on microsoft inspiration sir terry matthews  david thomas knights of the new technology key porter books   alcatel buys newbridge cnnmoney  february    mitel to acquire intertel tmcnetcom  april  retrieved  july    mitel becomes a public company – again ucstrategiescom  april    mitel networks buys aastra technologies in friendly takeover deal to create bigger hightech player press rele